# Manual example 1 (switch.md:37): four inputs I1..I4 to one output O1, stepped
# by a trigger at `forward`. Start: I1->O1. Each forward advances to the next
# input, wrapping I4->I1. `output` is the documented synonym for `output1`.
patch <<<
[switch]
    input1 = I1
    input2 = I2
    input3 = I3
    input4 = I4
    output = O1
    forward = I8
>>>
@0 set I1 0.1
@0 set I2 0.2
@0 set I3 0.3
@0 set I4 0.4
@0 expect O1 0.1
@1 set I8 1
@1 expect O1 0.2
@2 set I8 0
@3 set I8 1
@3 expect O1 0.3
@4 set I8 0
@5 set I8 1
@5 expect O1 0.4
@6 set I8 0
@7 set I8 1
@7 expect O1 0.1
